<TITLE> Flights at ZIA grounded over hurricane </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 16 (bdnews24.com)  Flight operations in Zia International Airport remained suspended early Friday as cyclone SIDR pierced through Khulna-Barisal coastline. Civil aviation official Saber Ahmed told bdnews24.com at 12:30am that no flights had taken off or touched down at the airport after 9:30pm Thursday. Flight operations at Shah Amanat International Airport in Chittagong also remained suspended since late Wednesday. Weather office in Dhaka earlier in the day advised authorities at ZIA to halt all flights from 9pm until further notice. One elderly man died in Satkhira Thursday evening as a boat sank in the cyclonic storm. Details of the devastation the cyclone left in its wake were sketchy. The capital Dhaka was battered by driving rains coupled with strong winds overnight. bdnews24
